cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL. 

The paper discusses a new probabilistic generative model that uses a CNN to design the prior distribution, and generates images from coarse to finer scales. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also introduces a new regularizer based on paths rendered in the generative model for training CNNs, which suggests that it could belong to the sub-category of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses a new loss function and a new deep network architecture, which suggests that it could belong to the sub-category of computation and language (cs.CL).
